        Official Singles Chart on 14/8/2020

        14 August 2020 - 20 August 2020

        The Official UK Singles Chart reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1 and MTV, the Top 100 is published exclusively on OfficialCharts.com. View the biggest songs of 2024 so far.

        WEEKLY CHART REVIEW (14/08/2020 - 20/08/2020)

        🔴 (Negative)

        1) Sadly, I don’t get the appeal behind Cardi B! She’s got charisma & an okay flow, but her content is always so disgusting. Not even Megan Thee Stallion can save this for me!

        2) Another D-Block Europe song?! They make the same thing everytime. This is getting old now!

        3) Not impressed with ‘Take You Dancing’ either unfortunately! The vocal beat on the hook is even more annoying than ‘Savage Love’ in my opinion.

        4) All of Taylor’s tracks fell again this week, with ‘The 1’ not even in the Top 40 anymore!

        5) ‘Dinner Guest’ is now on ACR, but at least ‘West Ten’ is still doing incredibly well.

        🟠 (Mixed)

        1) ‘Savage Love’ should be placed on ACR for the next chart! I can tolerate the song a lot more than most here, but even I think it’s getting old already (especially with all that overplay).

        2) ‘Dancing In The Moonlight’ got denied a Top 10 spot again, but I think it’ll still get there at some point with those sales & airplay numbers (also going up on streaming too!).

        3) As for ‘Men III’... the delivery & sincerity is deep, but why do many songs have to reference this pandemic?! As from that, the production could’ve hit a bit harder to make this really good.

        4) ‘Kings & Queens’ moved back into the Top 20, saved from ACR by the remix with Saweetie & Lauv!

        5) ‘Holiday’ randomly rebounded out of nowhere! I’m still indifferent on it though, even if Perrie shined on it once again (as she usually does).

        6) On first listen, ‘Smile’ sounds decent, especially The Weeknd’s vocals! I think this might move up into the “positive” section with time, because I think it could grow on me.

        7) ‘Dance Monkey’ finally left! Given that it charted about a year ago, it’s about time, despite being a decent song.

        8) ‘For The Night’ moved up again! Not one of Pop Smoke’s best sadly, but the tributes for him are really coming through now.

        🟢 (Positive)

        1) ‘Head & Heart’ held on for a fourth week! It doesn’t appear to be going anywhere either, given that BuzzJack reported it has a 15-20k sales lead this week.

        2) I don’t like TikTok as a streaming service, but I’m happy that it was responsible for getting ‘Mood Swings’ into the Top 10!

        3) ‘Heaven On My Mind’ is moving closer to the Top 10! I really hope it makes it before September.

        4) Chuffed to see ‘Looking For Me’ slowly becoming the newest EDM smash!

        5) ‘Fake Friends’ is coming for the Top 20, which is awesome to see!

        6) ‘What’s Love Got To Do With It’ rebounded! Another awesome remake of a 80’s classic from one of my all-time favourite DJ’s.

        7) Finally, ‘Hallucinate’ is here! It might’ve got here a couple weeks later than expected, but it’s cool that it made the Top 40 on the same day that the ‘Levitating’ remix was released (that might chart next week!).

        8) Not entirely chart-related, but the Discord live thread was so much fun tonight!

        9) Taylor Swift managed to retain her albums chart reign, despite close competition from Glass Animals & Deep Purple.

        That's it from me! Have a good weekend everyone. :)
